**** 2014/06/24 -- periodic tests

-- trig -- periodic  -- second-order (due to force integration)

  conv.p tbm.conv -model=linearBeam -tz=trig -bcn=per -tf=1. -cg=line -ng=4
                grid  & N &  $\vert w \vert$   & r
               Line5 &     5 & 1.88e-02 &
              Line10 &    10 & 5.31e-03 &  3.5
              Line20 &    20 & 1.35e-03 &  3.9
              Line40 &    40 & 3.39e-04 &  4.0
Convergence rates: c0=1.94


**** 2014/06/24 -- create the conv tests for tbm

=== Standing wave:

conv.p tbm.conv -model=linearBeam -tz=sw -bcn=p -tf=1. -Em=1. -T=0. -cg=line -ng=5



=== Test the "string" Em=0, T=1

String model needs a smaller cfl (??)
conv.p tbm.conv -model=linearBeam -tz=trig -bcn=p -tf=1. -Em=0. -T=1. -cg=line -cfl=.25 -suffix=string -ng=4

                grid  & N &  $\vert w \vert$   & r
               Line5 &     5 & 2.66e-02 &
              Line10 &    10 & 7.33e-03 &  3.6
              Line20 &    20 & 2.55e-03 &  2.9
              Line40 &    40 & 6.43e-04 &  4.0
              Line80 &    80 & 1.61e-04 &  4.0
Convergence rates: c0=1.82


